isoiec80000:term-t13-20-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "error probability"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t13-20-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "P"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t13-20 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "13-20" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t13-20-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t13-20-0 ;
  skos:definition """probability that a data element be incorrectly received"""@en ;
  skos:note """For the unit one, see the <<intro>>.

A subscript referring to a specified data element can
be added to the symbol.

[example]
error probability for binary digits or bit error
probability, stem:[P_{\"bit\"}]; +
block error probability, stem:[P_{\"bl\"}].

The measured value is designated as \"error ratio\",
whereas \"error rate\" is deprecated, for example, \"bit
error ratio\" (BER), \"block error ratio\".

See <<iec60050-171,droploc%locality:item=\"171-06-08\">>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-13 .